What to do to configure debian the way I like

Add thales	ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL to /etc/sudoers

Add shortcut Ctrl Alt T to xfce4-terminal (Settings -> Keyboard)

Add "setxkbmap -option caps:swapescape" to ~/.profile or to Session Start up
move  arrows_remap to .config/keyboard/ and add "xmodmap .config/keyboard/arrows_remap" to .profile

Install (command line programs):
htop
git
vim
zsh (after install, run: chsh -s /usr/bin/zsh thales)
oh-my-zsh 
tmux (Edit -> Preferences -> Run custom command ...: tmux) (
oh-my-tmux
tmux-ressurect
pathogen (create .vim autoload/pathogen.vim bundle)

Vim plugins
nerdtree
ctrlp
lightline
tpope/fugitive
tpope/comment (i didnt used it so far)
eskk (japanese input dic)

Install (other programs):
synapse (run with startup) or albert
paraview
spyder (python2)
spyder3 (python3)
wps-office
texmaker
chrome to linux
dropbox
Mendeley
Anki
